{"id":28,"parent_id":0,"book_id":80,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":28,"title":"Chapter 25: Aaron Teaches King Lamoni’s Father","subtitle":"","short_title":"Chapter 25","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-25-aaron-teaches-king-lamonis-father","content":[["div",{"id":"container","role":"main"},["div",{"type":"chapter","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-25-aaron-teaches-king-lamonis-father"},[".heading",{"id":"head1","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-25-aaron-teaches-king-lamonis-father.head1"},[".titleNumber","Chapter 25"],["h1","Aaron Teaches King Lamoni’s Father"]],[".bodyBlock",[".image",{"id":"f1","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-25-aaron-teaches-king-lamonis-father.f1"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_028_01.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p3","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-25-aaron-teaches-king-lamonis-father.p3"},"The Spirit guided Aaron and his companions to the land of Nephi to teach Lamoni’s father, the king over all the Lamanites."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p4","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-25-aaron-teaches-king-lamonis-father.p4"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/22.1"},"Alma 22:1"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f2","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-25-aaron-teaches-king-lamonis-father.f2"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_028_02.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p5","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-25-aaron-teaches-king-lamonis-father.p5"},"Aaron told the king he was Ammon’s brother. The king had been thinking about Ammon’s kindness and about what Ammon had said to him."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p6","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-25-aaron-teaches-king-lamonis-father.p6"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/22.2-3"},"Alma 22:2–3"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f3","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-25-aaron-teaches-king-lamonis-father.f3"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_028_03.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p7","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-25-aaron-teaches-king-lamonis-father.p7"},"Aaron asked the king if he believed in God. The king said he wasn’t sure but said he would believe if Aaron said God exists. Aaron assured the king that God lives."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p8","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-25-aaron-teaches-king-lamonis-father.p8"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/22.7-8"},"Alma 22:7–8"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f4","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-25-aaron-teaches-king-lamonis-father.f4"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_028_04.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p9","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-25-aaron-teaches-king-lamonis-father.p9"},"Aaron read the scriptures to the king. He taught him about the earth’s Creation, Adam’s Fall, and Jesus Christ’s mission."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p10","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-25-aaron-teaches-king-lamonis-father.p10"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/22.12-14"},"Alma 22:12–14"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f5","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-25-aaron-teaches-king-lamonis-father.f5"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_028_05.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p11","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-25-aaron-teaches-king-lamonis-father.p11"},"The king asked what he needed to do to have the Holy Ghost and be ready to live with God. The king was willing to do anything, even give up his kingdom."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p12","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-25-aaron-teaches-king-lamonis-father.p12"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/22.15"},"Alma 22:15"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f6","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-25-aaron-teaches-king-lamonis-father.f6"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_028_06.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p13","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-25-aaron-teaches-king-lamonis-father.p13"},"Aaron told the king he needed to fully repent of his sins. He needed to pray and have faith in God."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p14","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-25-aaron-teaches-king-lamonis-father.p14"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/22.16"},"Alma 22:16"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f7","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-25-aaron-teaches-king-lamonis-father.f7"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_028_07.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p15","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-25-aaron-teaches-king-lamonis-father.p15"},"The king prayed to know if there really is a God. He said he would give up all his sins."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p16","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-25-aaron-teaches-king-lamonis-father.p16"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/22.17-18"},"Alma 22:17–18"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f8","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-25-aaron-teaches-king-lamonis-father.f8"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_028_08.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p17","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-25-aaron-teaches-king-lamonis-father.p17"},"The king fell to the ground and appeared to be dead. When the queen saw him, she thought Aaron and his companions had killed him."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p18","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-25-aaron-teaches-king-lamonis-father.p18"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/22.19"},"Alma 22:19"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f9","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-25-aaron-teaches-king-lamonis-father.f9"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_028_09.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p19","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-25-aaron-teaches-king-lamonis-father.p19"},"The queen ordered her servants to kill Aaron and his companions, but the servants were afraid to. She sent them to find other people who would do it."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p20","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-25-aaron-teaches-king-lamonis-father.p20"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/22.20-21"},"Alma 22:20–21"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f10","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-25-aaron-teaches-king-lamonis-father.f10"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_028_10.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p21","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-25-aaron-teaches-king-lamonis-father.p21"},"Before a large crowd could gather and cause trouble, Aaron took the king’s hand and told him to stand. The king stood."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p22","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-25-aaron-teaches-king-lamonis-father.p22"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/22.22"},"Alma 22:22"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f11","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-25-aaron-teaches-king-lamonis-father.f11"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_028_11.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p23","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-25-aaron-teaches-king-lamonis-father.p23"},"The king calmed his frightened wife and servants and then taught them the gospel. They all believed in Jesus Christ."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p24","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-25-aaron-teaches-king-lamonis-father.p24"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/22.23"},"Alma 22:23"]]]]]]]],"refs":null}
